To the people who complain that they can't get the support that they want/need/deserve, volunteer and become a Guide. They are constantly looking for Guides. Why? Because the game is always expanding and Guiding can't be easy. I mean, just dealing with the normal problem that can happen, you have to deal with people who train the Guards and Bards to the North Freeport tunnels (When doing a corpse recovery for a friend, I heard one moron state, &quot;But it wouldn't be called a train if everybody liked it.&quot;), people who argue over the kill stealing of an Orc Centurian, and someone insisting that they get a rezz because they were killed when they when LD (because LD is &quot;obviously&quot; caused by Verant). ( see <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tweety.bowlofmice.com/tweety/try_being_a_guide.html">Try Being a Guide</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ). If you don't like the current level a service, become a Guide yourself ( <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://guide.everquest.com/guideapp/">Guide Application</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> ) In my two years (next month) of playing Everquest, I have only met one Guide I didn't much care for (and I saw his point, I just didn't agree with it). <br>
<br>
People complain of the quests (which I personally tend to avoid because of lag) is that if they are part of a story, some people go out of their way to ruin it for those of us that would like to watch. If it is a kill-fest quest, people complain about that too. What kind of quest do you want? How should it be implimented. Instead of complaining, why can't people use the /feedback command?<br>
<br>
From what was said, some of these features may trickle to the normal server. That would be great. Weither it does or doesn't isn't really important to me. Even with any faults with the game, I still like Everquest and I still play five nights a week. <p><BR>
